node.title: SA bans NT travellers from coming to state as Top End COVID-19 cases grow
node.alt: A photo of cars on the road
node.description: Only South Australians will be able to return from the Northern Territory, as an outbreak in Katherine and the remote community of Robinson River continue to grow.
node.content: ["Only South Australians will be able to return from the Northern Territory, as the number of COVID-19 cases continues to grow in the Top End.", "The cluster between Katherine and Robinson River now stands at 19 cases.", "Fully vaccinated South Australians who have been in the Katherine council area since November 10 will be allowed to return home but will have to do a seven-day quarantine, SA Police said in a direction issued this evening.", "Unvaccinated South Australians who have been in the area will have to quarantine for 14 days.", "People returning from other areas of the Northern Territory will have to get COVID-19 tests on their first, fifth and 13th day in South Australia.", "Residents of the Northern Territory or other states will not be able to enter South Australia.", "More to come."]
